article.description:
Rookie Tamika Catchings drilled five 3-pointers and matched a season high with 32 points as the
Indiana Fever extended their winning streak to four games with a 70-63 victory over the Orlando Miracle.
article.headline: Fever, Miracle tied for final playoff spot
article.linkText: Catchings scores 32 as Fever pull even with Miracle
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Tamika Catchings matched her franchise
record with 32 points and had 12 rebounds as the Indiana Fever beat
the Orlando Miracle 70-63 on Wednesday night.

	   Catchings, the rookie star from Tennessee who leads the WNBA in
scoring, was 5-for-9 from 3-point range to help Indiana (14-15) move
into a fourth-place tie with Orlando in the Eastern Conference.

	   "This is what we've been waiting for,'' Catchings said. "This
is definitely what the franchise has been talking about since we've
come around.''

	   She scored 22 points in the first half, 13 in a 3½-minute span.

	   "You saw, in my mind, the MVP of this league tonight,'' Fever
coach Nell Fortner said. "At this point in the season, this kid is
playing phenomenal basketball.''

	   Coquese Washington added 10 points and a franchise-record 11
assists in the Fever's fourth straight victory, also a club best.
Indiana is 6-2 since acquiring Washington from Houston.

	   Wendy Palmer, Nykesha Sales and Katie Douglas each scored 15
points for the Miracle.

	   "It's exciting to have a chance to make the playoffs,'' Douglas
said. "I didn't really get to be a part of it last year, so I
really want to get back to the playoffs this year and be a bigger
part of it.''
